Dumb-TV dev kit -- third-party components
=========================================

The dev kit's own source (everything in this directory) is released under
CC0 1.0 Universal (public domain) -- see LICENSE.

At runtime it uses these libraries, each under its own license (installed
separately by pip / the launcher, not part of this source):

  numpy          BSD 3-Clause License
  pygame         GNU LGPL v2.1
  opencv-python  Apache License 2.0  (bundles FFmpeg, GNU LGPL v2.1)   [optional]

If you redistribute a BUNDLED build (e.g. one produced with PyInstaller), include
these libraries' license texts alongside it. The LGPL components (pygame, and
FFmpeg via opencv-python) are dynamically linked; a PyInstaller *onedir* build
keeps them as separate, replaceable files, which satisfies the LGPL relinking
requirement. If you don't ship real-video decoding, omit opencv-python/FFmpeg
entirely -- the sim runs on synthetic patterns with just numpy + pygame.

The vendored SERV RISC-V core (../rtl/serv) is ISC + Apache-2.0; see its own
LICENSE. It is not part of the dev kit runtime (the dev kit uses its own
pure-Python RV32I emulator).
